AI Disruption
-------------

AI is obviously the other major theme of 2024, just as it was in 2023, and =
just as it is poised to be for many years to come. This year=E2=80=99s core=
 model advances, particularly on the leading edge, felt less dramatic than =
2023; advances beyond GPT-4 were more iterative, although o1 was a big leap=
 in a new direction, while there were massive gains in terms of efficiency =
=E2=80=94 there are now a whole host of models with GPT-4 level capability =
that were dramatically cheaper to build and are much cheaper to serve.

That, though, only sets the stage for 2025 and what I expect to be a wave o=
f new companies that are built around AI from the ground up. Some of the mo=
st vulnerable companies will not be old-line real-world companies, but rath=
er relatively young SaaS companies that will be vulnerable to not only a te=
chnological revolution but a business disruption: if the biggest economic i=
mpact of AI will be eliminating jobs ( https://stratechery.com/2024/enterpr=
ise-philosophy-and-the-first-wave-of-ai/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiI=
